<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>••••••••••vs••••••••••</strong></h1>
<h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #b23233;"><em><strong><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="269330" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/what-is-the-best-literary-film-adaptation-of-the-last-50-years/muchado-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado.jpg" data-orig-size="800,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="muchado" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado.jpg" class="aligncenter wp-image-269330" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="281" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado-300x169.jpg 300w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado-768x432.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado-60x34.jpg 60w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/muchado-50x28.jpg 50w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" />Much Ado About Nothing</strong></em></span><br />
dir. Kenneth Branagh, 1993</h1>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Based on </strong>William Shakespeare’s <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780743482752" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Much Ado About Nothing</a></em> (1600)</h5>
<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Sub-genres: </strong> Ye Olde Jokes • Ample Bosoms • Eating His Heart in the Marketplace • By Shakespeare Nerds, For Shakespeare Nerds</h5>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>There’s a never-ending set of Shakespeare adaptations out there but there’s something simply perfect about Kenneth Branagh’s crack at <em>Much Ado</em>, one of the best plays in the canon. Branagh can get self-indulgent in his later work, but this one zips along like the frothy comedy it is, with absolutely radiant turns from Branagh and Emma Thompson and Denzel Washington and Imelda Staunton and, yes, even the much-maligned Keanu Reeves, who brings a particularly human darkness to the too-often-too-cartoonish Don John. Everybody seems to be having a damn good time, it’s all very &#8217;90s, I wish more adaptations would have fun like this one does. <em>–Drew Broussard, Podcast Editor</em></p>
