<p>You can hear the sweeping John Williams right now, I&#8217;m sure, a sign of how indelible this movie has become. <em>Jurassic Park</em> is a classic, full of great performances, endlessly quotable lines, and all those dinosaurs moving in herds. It&#8217;s quintessentially summer. It&#8217;s so good that even the atrocious sequels can’t take the shine off of it.</p>
<p>One thing I’ve always wondered is that if Jurassic Park were real, would the park have the equivalent of annoying Disney Adults, whose entire personalities revolve around the dinos? It&#8217;s just one of the reasons I&#8217;m glad this is fiction. <em>–JF</em></p>
